Germany's 1st autochthonous (indigenous) human West Nile virus infection was reported in late September 2019; see at https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/west-nile-virus-climate-change-mosquito-germany-tropical-medicine-a9123601.html (thanks to Sabine Zentis).

A European update on infections in humans and outbreaks in animals, as of 18 Oct 2019, is available at https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/west-nile-fever/surveillance-and-disease-data/disease-data-ecdc. - Mod.AS

